  <static seed="1479" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalLiteralEquations/LiteralEquation290.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve this equation for <m>p</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{1}{m} = \frac{3}{p+9} }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="7" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>p = 3m-9</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To solve this equation, we multiple both sides with the common denominator <m>{m\mathopen{}\left(p+9\right)}</m>:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{1}{m} \amp = \frac{3}{p+9}   \\
   \frac{1}{m} \cdot m(p+9) \amp = \frac{3}{p+9} \cdot m(p+9) \\
   p+9 \amp = 3m \\
   p \amp = 3m - 9
\end{aligned}
}</m></p>
</solution>
